es of exoplanets\ntransiting bright stars. We obtain a flat transmission spectrum for HAT-P-26b\nin the range of 490-900 nm that can be explained by the presence of a grey\nopacity cloud deck, and indications of transit timing variations, both of which\nare consistent with previous measurements.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 13 Dec 2021 13:54:40 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-12-14"}
