{"id":"2112.06737","submitter":"Jona Lelmi","authors":"Tim Laux and Jona Lelmi","title":"Large data limit of the MBO scheme for data clustering:\n  $\\Gamma$-convergence of the thresholding energies","comments":"Added Corollary 1. Corrected some typos and updated references","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"math.AP math.DG","license":"http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/","abstract":"  In this work we begin to rigorously analyze the MBO scheme for data\nclustering in the large data limit. Each iteration of the MBO scheme\ncorresponds to one step of implicit gradient descent for the thresholding\nenergy on the similarity graph of some dataset. For a subset of the nodes of\nthe graph, the thresholding energy at time $h$ is the amount of heat\ntransferred from the subset to its complement at time $h$, rescaled by a factor\n$\\sqrt{h}$. It is then natural to think that outcomes of the MBO scheme are\n(local) minimizers of this energy. We prove that the algorithm is consistent,\nin the sense that these (local) minimizers converge to minimizers of a suitably\nweighted optimal partition problem.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 13 Dec 2021 15:43:43 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 15 Dec 2021 16:53:46 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Sun, 26 Jun 2022 19:54:02 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Wed, 10 Aug 2022 14:02:16 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-08-11"}
